abstract: Specializing in fashionable flatbreads, Gleason’s shows both admirable restraint and whimsicality. The restaurant opened in August.
snippet: Specializing in fashionable flatbreads, Gleason’s shows both admirable restraint and whimsicality. The restaurant opened in August.
lead_paragraph: GLEASON’S, which opened in August in Peekskill, joins a thriving patch of scrappy, recession-era eating spots that have sprung up locally — like so many hardy lettuces — in a forbidding economic climate.

abstract: On Sept. 18, the Texas Heart Institute celebrated its 50th anniversary by honoring its 93-year-old founder, Denton A. Cooley.
snippet: On Sept. 18, the Texas Heart Institute celebrated its 50th anniversary by honoring its 93-year-old founder, Denton A. Cooley.
lead_paragraph: Every once in a while, there are moments in Houston that provide a vivid glimpse of the city that was — that aggressively entrepreneurial, insanely individualistic and relentlessly optimistic place of lore. Such a moment was visible the night of Sept. 18, when the Texas Heart Institute celebrated its 50th anniversary by honoring its founder, Denton A. Cooley, whose name is almost always accompanied by the description “world-famous heart surgeon.”

abstract: Stephen Burt, the Harvard professor and poet, has many brilliant peers in his generation of poetry critics, and if one doesn’t inspire you to read poetry, another might.
snippet: Stephen Burt, the Harvard professor and poet, has many brilliant peers in his generation of poetry critics, and if one doesn’t inspire you to read poetry, another might.
lead_paragraph: Stephen Burt, the Harvard professor and poet whom I wrote about in Sunday’s Education Issue, is a fanboy and an evangelist of poetry. As I wrote in the magazine, Burt defends his positivity by saying, “There’s so little airtime available for any poetry these days that when I get space and time in which I can do whatever I want, I don’t want to say, ‘X sucks.’ I almost always prefer to say, ‘Please check out Y,’ or ‘Z isn’t what you think,’ or ‘Look at what A, B and C have in common.’ ”

abstract: Some longtime fans of the University of Montana Grizzlies are wrestling with their feelings in the wake of a series of allegations of sexual assaults by football players.
snippet: Some longtime fans of the University of Montana Grizzlies are wrestling with their feelings in the wake of a series of allegations of sexual assaults by football players.
lead_paragraph: MISSOULA, Mont. — Students are back in their classrooms this week, the heat of summer has cooled and new chalk lines have been placed on the football field as the University of Montana Grizzlies and their devoted fans prepare for the opening kickoff on Saturday.
